Dragons assistant coach Shaun Connor: "We knew there was going to be a reaction from last week against the Blues and they came to try and slow the game down and play at their pace and it worked for them in the end.
"I thought we started pretty well. We felt if we were accurate in the first half hour we could have scored a few tries and then the game would have opened up for us in the second half.
"But because we weren't accurate it was a bit of a dog-fight in the end but it's a win for us. There's lots to work on but we'll take four points."
